sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.core

Class ForwardingResource<L extends Listener>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.common.collect.ForwardingObject
      • sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.core.ForwardingRegistrable
        • sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.core.ForwardingResource<L>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Nameable, Registrable, Resource<L>

    public abstract class ForwardingResource<L extends Listener>
extends ForwardingRegistrable
implements Resource<L>
    A resource which forwards all its method calls to another resource. Subclasses should override one or more methods to modify the behavior of the backing resource as desired per the decorator pattern.

    Note that this class does not forward the equals and hashCode methods through to the backing object. See ForwardingObject for more details.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Pavol Zbell
